Chelsea Wants Zola, Hiddink as Ancelotti Faces Exit: Soccer Roundup

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-05-10T09:42:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/chelsea-wants-zola-hiddink-as-ancelotti-faces-exit-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  Zola, Hiddink Sought  Chelsea owner  Roman Abramovich  wants Gianfranco Zola to
return as a member of the coaching staff next season, the  Daily
Mirror  reported.  Abramovich will also make a “final plea” to Guus Hiddink
to come back as replacement for coach Carlo Ancelotti, who’s on
the way out, the newspaper added.  The billionaire owner is ready to pay Hiddink 6 million
pounds ($9.8 million) a year, the  Daily Express  said.  Tevez for Real Madrid?  Real Madrid coach  Jose Mourinho  has made Carlos Tevez his
No. 1 transfer target this summer,  the Mirror  reported.  Mourinho wants to link the Manchester City striker with his
former Manchester United teammate Cristiano Ronaldo, the Mirror
said.  City ‘Unstoppable’  Tottenham manager  Harry Redknapp  said Manchester City is
“unstoppable” because of its financial firepower, and he
predicted the Abu Dhabi-owned club will sign top players in the
coming offseason,  the Express  reported.  “They’ve got unlimited funds and won’t stop until they win
the championship and even then the Champions League,” Redknapp
said.  City, nearing a Champions League berth for the first time,
hosts Tottenham tonight.  Gunner Karim?  Arsenal may try to sign Real Madrid striker Karim Benzema
for 20 million pounds, according to  Metro .  The Frenchman is out of favor at the Spanish club and coach
Jose Mourinho is looking to raise funds for new recruits, the
newspaper added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty in  London  at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
